general.description:
Over 35 years international financial services experience, 22 years experience as non-executive company director of multiple ASX top-10 companies as well as a top-10 UK company.  Boards have included banking, investment management, retail as well as Qantas, the iconic Australian airline. Patricia has served on many honorary and not for profit boards in the public and private sector, including as a founding member of the Grattan Institute and as the founding Chairman of the 30% Club in Australia. Prior to board career, Patricia worked in senior executive financial services executive positions for over 15 years in U.S., Europe and Australia running international treasury and financial markets teams for very large global financial institutions. and prior to that in the U.S. government.  Awarded Life Fellow Australian Institute of Company Directors #AICD, Founding Chair 30percent Club Australia #30pctAustralia, Member WomenCorporateDirectors #WCD, Received a Centenary Award in 2001 for services to the Australian community in financial services.

Expert in financial markets, investment banking, funds management, corporate governance.

@PatriciaACross

jobs.description:
I was part of a team that manages and co-ordinates international litigation strategy for multi-national clients. My particular experience included:

•	acting for a major US-based energy company in an expert determination concerning the price of natural gas under a long term supply contract;

•	acting for a leading company in the UK nuclear industry with respect to negotiations surrounding the purchase of a nuclear facility from the UK government;

•	•	acting for various UK-based financial institutions in relation to issues and disputes arising from the collapse of the Icelandic banking industry; and

•	acting for consumer goods companies in international class action and product liability litigation.

As a litigation associate at Blakes, my practice included barristerial work. My particular experience included:

•	appearing for a Canadian-based energy company in a prosecution relating to the production of waste product ash;

•	acting for a major US manufacturer and distributor of mechanical heart valves in a major product liability class action;

•	acting for a major US manufacturer of pharmaceuticals and medical devices in various product liability class actions and disputes; and

•	appearing for a US based bank in an action relating to consumer credit card conditions.

Key partner to the leadership team on strategic acquisitions and integration;
      management of organsiational change and development of communication strategies;
